---

<AdminLayout
  title="Info Box Components"
  description="Create dynamic and informative status indicators with customizable info boxes"
  currentPath="interface/info-box"
  enableComponentPreview={true}
  enableToc={true}
>
  <PageHeader {...pageHeaderConfiguration} />
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-10 order-1 order-md-0">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-12">
          <p class="my-0">
            Info boxes are essential UI components for displaying key metrics, statistics, and
            status updates in a clear and engaging way. They combine icons, text, and visual
            indicators to present information at a glance while maintaining a professional and
            modern appearance.
          </p>
          <div class="alert alert-info mt-3">
            <i class="ri-lightbulb-line me-2"></i>
            <strong>Design Tip:</strong> For optimal visual hierarchy, use consistent icon styles and
            color schemes across related info boxes. Consider using contrasting colors for different
            data categories to improve scanability.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row js-toc-content">
        <div class="col-12">
          <!-- Basic Info Box Section -->
          <div class="my-3">
            <h3 class="mb-0" id="basic-info-box">Basic Info Box</h3>
            <p class="py-2">
              Basic info boxes provide a clean and straightforward way to display metrics. Each box
              combines an icon with a colored background and content area, making it perfect for
              highlighting key statistics or status information.
            </p>
            <ComponentPreview
              title="Basic Info Box Examples"
              height="450px"
              component={basicInfoBoxExample}
              htmlCode={basicInfoBoxExample}
            />
          </div>

          <!-- Background Info Box Section -->
          <div class="my-3">
            <h3 class="mb-0" id="background-info-box">Background Info Box</h3>
            <p class="py-2">
              Background info boxes enhance visual impact with full-color backgrounds and include
              progress bars for showing completion rates or progress metrics. These are ideal for
              dashboards and analytics displays.
            </p>
            <ComponentPreview
              title="Background Info Box Examples"
              height="550px"
              component={backgroundInfoBoxExample}
              htmlCode={backgroundInfoBoxExample}
            />
          </div>

          <!-- Outline Info Box Section -->
          <div class="my-3">
            <h3 class="mb-0" id="outline-info-box">Outline Info Box</h3>
            <p class="py-2">
              Outline info boxes offer a lighter visual alternative with bordered styles. They
              maintain high readability while providing a more subtle appearance, perfect for
              secondary metrics or less critical information.
            </p>
            <ComponentPreview
              title="Outline Info Box Examples"
              height="450px"
              component={outlineInfoBoxExample}
              htmlCode={outlineInfoBoxExample}
            />
          </div>

          <!-- Loading Info Box Section -->
          <div class="my-3">
            <h3 class="mb-0" id="loading-info-box">Loading Info Box</h3>
            <p class="py-2">
              Loading info boxes incorporate animated overlays to indicate active processes or data
              updates. They're essential for providing visual feedback during data fetching,
              synchronization, or processing operations.
            </p>
            <ComponentPreview
              title="Loading Info Box Examples"
              height="550px"
              component={loadingStateInfoBoxExample}
              htmlCode={loadingStateInfoBoxExample}
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-2 mb-4 order-0 order-md-1">
      <Toc />
    </div>
  </div>
</AdminLayout>
